 type of status consumption.
 The visibility-based social inference models assume that status consumption
 is futile in the regular sense - an assumption that ensures the separability
 of demand for visible goods in the direct utility model.
 A majority of empirical studies on visible consumption use these models
 to explain the significant role of social identities in visible consumption
 
